Powered by RubiQube Ad Network ADO-EKITI – A clergy,Prophet Ade Ologbonyo has urged churches to join hands with President Muhammadu Buhari in prayers to tackle the twin evils of banditry and kidnappings in the land . Prophet Ologbonyo,founder of the Christ Apostolic Church (CAC) Mercy Land ,Orun-Ekiti gave the admonition during its 10th anniversary and ground breaking ceremony of the 5000 capacity ultramodern church auditorium . The foundation laying was performed by the CAC District Coordinating Superintendent,Agege ,Pastor Olu Eyebiokin on behalf of the CAC General Evangelist, Prophet Hezekiah Oladeji . Speaking at the occasion, Prophet Ologbonyo who went down the memory lane said the church which begun with 20 worshippers in his sitting room had grown in leaps and bounds ,with branches in different states . He admonished his congregation not to waiver in their trust in God and do everything within their capacity to promote the words of God. On insecurity,the cleric said all hands must be on the deck in tackling the menace. “As men of God,I think we are duty bound to intensify our prayer for Nigeria and her leaders in order to get out of the prevailing challenges.What is happening in Nigeria today remains a source of concern and worry to all.The spate of insecurity had reached an alarming proportion as we all living in perpetual fear .Nobody can sleep with his or her two eyes closed.” the cleric lamented .” “Even in our community here ,there is palpable fear everywhere .In fact it got a point when I had joined in the night security surveillance in my community here.At times ,I used to visit as many as 15 communities in order to assure them and give them hope.The challenges confronting Nigeria is multiple faceted.Today,there is no job for our teeming unemployed youths ,the Hospitals are in bad shape ,the roads are also bad .So,there is no way any nation suffering from all these societal ills would not be faced by the challenge of insecurity .During one of my visits to our people in the community ,God used me to save a patient who would have died because of his inability to procure a three hundred naira worth of drugs .So,the situation of our people is as worse as that .It high time government done something about it “